    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="710"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A Pacific War/221a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-23">October 23,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2416. Request Swiss Government to inform its Minister Tokyo that this Government
                    has reports of Japanese radio broadcasts to the effect <pb facs="0836" n="824"
                        xml:id="pg_824"/> that the Japanese authorities intend to try before
                    military tribunals American prisoners of war for military operations and to
                    impose upon them severe penalties, including even the death penalty. Other
                    reports state that Japanese radio broadcasts are to the effect that such trials
                    have already taken place.</p>
                <p>Ask Swiss Minister urgently to report the facts regarding the foregoing. Also
                    request report, whether, in accordance with the Japanese Government’s
                    undertaking to apply the Geneva Prisoners of War Convention, Swiss
                    representatives have been permitted to visit the prisoners in question as
                    provided in Article 86 of the Convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
